-- Clover Industries May List Its Shares in Johannesburg, Business Day Says
-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 2010-10-01T05:00:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/clover-industries-may-list-its-shares-in-johannebsurg-business-day-says.html
Clover Industries Ltd. may start
trading its shares on the stock exchange in Johannesburg within
the next few months, Johannesburg’s Business Day newspaper said,
citing, Johann Vorster, the company’s chief executive officer.  Clover, the biggest buyer of fresh milk in South Africa,
has approval from its board to list, he said, according to the
newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  